claim.claim-text:
12. A surgical apparatus, the apparatus comprising:
an elongated body having a distal end and a proximal end;
first and second jaws operably extending from the distal end, at least one of the first and second jaw configured to move with respect to the elongated body;
a control handle operably connected to the proximal end, the control handle comprising an actuator that causes relative movement of the first jaw with respect to the second jaw;
a first heating element disposed on the first jaw and a second heating element disposed on one of the first and second jaws and wherein at least a portion of the first heating element comprises two welding portions that are spaced apart from one another and electrically connected in parallel.

20. A surgical apparatus comprising:
a shaft having a proximal region and a distal region;
first and second jaws extending from the distal region of the shaft, wherein the first jaw is relatively movable with respect to the second jaw;
a first electrode portion operatively associated with one of the first and second jaws and is adapted to weld tissue;
a second electrode portion operatively associated and fixedly attached with one of the first and second jaws and configured to have a different electrical resistance value than the first electrode portion, the second electrode portion is adapted to sever tissue upon the application of current therethrough; and
a control handle operably connected to the proximal region of the shaft;
wherein the first and second electrodes portions are connected in series.
